title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland Auditorium Arena on 1979-12-26
description: Cold Rain & Snow, CC Rider, Dire Wolf, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Brown Eyed Women, Minglewood Blues, Friend Of The Devil, Looks Like Rain, Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land Uncle John's Band-> Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> The Other One-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Brokedown Palace-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E:Shakedown Street-> E: Uncle John's Band

reviews.review_text: Great show, bad recording This recording does not do this show justice.  It is mostly a boomy audience recording with bits and pieces of really good sbd spliced in.  The splices are seemless but I don't know why they didn't just use the board for the whole show.
Dick's Picks #5 For those of you who may not know..

You should know this too. I have long had a great soundboard of the second set of this show sans encore.  When the Dick's came out I rushed out and bought it.  Whoever mastered the thing had sucked the life out of it.  It was my first major Dick Picks disappointment.  I have been disappointed many more times since.  Someone on the other site for this show says that it's second best after Pembroke Pines.  I love Pembroke but couldn't disagree more about the Oakland release.  My analog cassette tape kicks its ass all over the parking lot.
EH, Poor Sound It was a great show but this copy is not very good.
